<h2 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-=F0=9F=A7=A0AIArchitectureDetail=
s">=F0=9F=A7=A0 AI Architecture Details</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-ModelContextProtocol(MCP)Impleme=
ntation">Model Context Protocol (MCP) Implementation</h3>
<p><strong>What is MCP?</strong><br>
MCP is Anthropic's open standard for AI-tool communication - think of it as=
 USB for AI. It provides a universal protocol that allows any MCP-compatibl=
e AI to discover and use our 52 tools without custom integration code.</p>
<p><strong>MVP Implementation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>52 standardized tools spanning 7 modules (Calendar, Tasks, Lists, Expens=
es, Feed, Documents, Meals)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Automatic tool discovery and capability registration</p></li>
<li>
<p>Model-agnostic architecture (can switch from Gemini to GPT or Claude wit=
hout code changes)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Standardized request/response format across all tools</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Future-proof: Easy to add new AI models without rebuilding integrations<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>Maintainable: Single tool definition works across all AI agents</p></li>
<li>
<p>Industry standard: Growing ecosystem support from major AI providers</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-Agent-to-UI(A2UI)Technology">Age=
nt-to-UI (A2UI) Technology</h3>
<p><strong>What is A2UI?</strong><br>
A breakthrough capability where AI doesn't just respond with text=E2=80=94i=
t directly controls the mobile application interface. When you ask "show me=
 my tasks," the AI navigates to the tasks screen, highlights urgent items, =
and displays actionable buttons.</p>
<p><strong>MVP Implementation:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Component Registry</strong>: 15 key components (TaskList, Calend=
ar, ExpenseChart, etc.)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Navigation System</strong>: AI can switch between screens progra=
mmatically</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Highlighting Mechanism</strong>: Draw user attention to specific=
 UI elements</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>State Manipulation</strong>: Update, refresh, filter components =
on demand</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Action Execution</strong>: Mark tasks complete, add events, upda=
te budgets</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Phased Rollout:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Week 8</strong>: Foundation - Component registry, basic navigati=
on</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Week 9-10</strong>: Enhancement - Highlighting, state manipulati=
on, action execution</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Post-MVP</strong>: Advanced features - Contextual animations, co=
mplex workflows</p></li>
</ol>
<h2 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-=E2=9A=A0=EF=B8=8FOutofScope">=
=E2=9A=A0=EF=B8=8F Out of Scope</h2>
<p>Features intentionally excluded from MVP launch but may be revisited in =
future releases:</p>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-Phase2Features(Post-MVP-Months4-=
12)">Phase 2 Features (Post-MVP - Months 4-12)</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Advanced Analytics Dashboard</strong>: Detailed insights into fa=
mily patterns, productivity, and trends</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Third-Party Calendar Integrations</strong>: Google Calendar, App=
le Calendar, Outlook bidirectional sync</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Bank Account Integration</strong>: Automatic expense import from=
 financial institutions</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Smart Home Integration</strong>: IoT device control through fami=
ly assistant (lights, thermostats, locks)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Location-Based Services</strong>: Geofencing, location-aware rem=
inders, arrival notifications</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Social Features</strong>: Family-to-family sharing, playdate coo=
rdination, community events</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Advanced A2UI Features</strong>: Complex multi-step workflows, c=
ontextual animations, predictive UI</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-FutureConsiderations(12+Months)"=
>Future Considerations (12+ Months)</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Pet Care Module</strong>: Vet appointments, medication tracking,=
 feeding schedules, pet profiles</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Medication Tracking</strong>: Prescription reminders, refill not=
ifications, pharmacy integration</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Educational Module</strong>: Homework tracking, assignment deadl=
ines, parent-teacher communication</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Eldercare Features</strong>: Medical appointment coordination, c=
aregiver scheduling, health monitoring</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Multi-Language Support</strong>: Full internationalization beyon=
d English (Spanish, French, Mandarin)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>White-Label Platform</strong>: Enterprise B2B2C offering for emp=
loyee assistance programs</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Developer API Access</strong>: Third-party integrations and cust=
om automations</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>MCP Marketplace</strong>: Allow users to add custom MCP tools fo=
r specialized needs</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-TechnicalDebtIntentionallyDeferr=
ed">Technical Debt Intentionally Deferred</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Advanced Redis caching strategies beyond basic query caching</p></li>
<li>
<p>Horizontal scaling and multi-region deployment (single region MVP)</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>Advanced security features (biometric authentication, hardware security =
keys)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Comprehensive APM and error tracking (basic monitoring only)</p></li>
<li>
<p>Advanced AI features (sentiment analysis, predictive modeling beyond cur=
rent scope)</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-=F0=9F=8E=A8Design">=F0=9F=8E=A8=
 Design</h2>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-DesignSystem">Design System</h3>
<p><strong>Figma Files:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://www.figma.com/design/dN933eYk=
QKEuP05RbydIBV/Home-OS?node-id=3D0-1&amp;t=3DNYT9NQP5Sys0kLTx-1" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">Home OS - Complete Design System</a></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-DesignPrinciples">Design Princip=
les</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p><strong>Voice-First, Touch-Second</strong>: Primary interaction through =
voice with touch as intuitive fallback</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Contextual Simplicity</strong>: Show only what's relevant to cur=
rent user context and task</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Family-Centric Design</strong>: Accommodates multiple users with=
 varying ages and tech literacy levels</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Accessible by Default</strong>: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum a=
cross all interfaces</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Unified Experience</strong>: Consistent design language across m=
obile (iOS/Android) and web admin panel</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>AI-Driven UI</strong>: Interface adapts based on AI recommendati=
ons and A2UI control</p></li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-KeyScreens&amp;UserFlows">Key Sc=
reens &amp; User Flows</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Family Dashboard</strong>: Aggregate view of all family activity=
, upcoming events, pending tasks</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Calendar View</strong>: Day/week/month views with AI conflict hi=
ghlighting and suggestions</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Task Management</strong>: List view with filters, AI assignment =
suggestions, completion tracking</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Grocery &amp; Shopping Lists</strong>: Categorized lists with lo=
cation-aware notifications</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Expense Tracker</strong>: Transaction log with receipt scanning,=
 split calculations, budget progress</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Family Feed</strong>: Chronological activity stream with photos,=
 comments, reactions</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Document Vault</strong>: Secure storage with categories, OCR sea=
rch, expiration tracking</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Meal Planner</strong>: Weekly calendar view with recipe cards, n=
utritional info, grocery integration</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Voice Interface</strong>: Visual feedback with waveform, transcr=
iption display, AI response bubbles</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>AI Control Indicators</strong>: Visual cues when AI is navigatin=
g or manipulating UI (A2UI in action)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-DesignTokens">Design Tokens</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Color Palette</strong>: Warm, inviting family-friendly colors (p=
rimary blue, accent orange, neutral grays)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Typography</strong>: Inter for UI elements, system fonts optimiz=
ed for performance</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Spacing System</strong>: Consistent 8px grid system for all layo=
ut spacing</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Iconography</strong>: Lucide React icon library for consistency =
and performance</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Motion Design</strong>: Smooth 200-300ms transitions, purposeful=
 animations only</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>AI Highlights</strong>: Special color treatments for AI-controll=
ed elements (subtle glow, border)</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"ProductRequirementsDocument(PRD)-=E2=9D=93Openquestions">=E2=9D=
=93 Open questions</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Question</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Answer</strong></p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p><strong>Date Answered</strong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What should the final application name be?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Under consideration: Hearth, Otto, Maple, Nora (character-first names)</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How do we handle voice recognition accuracy for children ages 5-10?</p><=
/td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Test with beta families; may need age-specific models or text fallback</=
p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Should we integrate existing calendars (Google/Apple) for MVP?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Deferred to Phase 2 to reduce complexity and external dependencies</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How do we ensure data privacy for sensitive family documents?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>AES-256 encryption at rest, TLS 1.3 in transit, PostgreSQL RLS isolation=
</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What's our fallback if Google denies startup credits?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Use GCP free tier, optimize costs further, or evaluate AWS/Azure alterna=
tives</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How do we handle family member removal (divorce, estrangement)?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Soft delete with 30-day retention, full data export option before remova=
l</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Should we support non-traditional family structures?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Yes - design for flexibility: multi-generational, single parent, extende=
d family</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How do we measure "cognitive load reduction" quantitatively?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Proxy metrics: time saved (surveys), AI usage frequency, task delegation=
 balance</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What's onboarding strategy for non-technical users (elderly, children)?<=
/p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Interactive tutorial, voice-guided setup, optional human onboarding for =
Premium</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How do we prevent AI hallucinations affecting family coordination?</p></=
td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Confidence thresholds, human confirmation for critical actions, comprehe=
nsive audit logs</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>How complex should initial A2UI interactions be?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Start simple (navigation, highlighting), expand to complex workflows pos=
t-MVP</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Can we deliver both MCP and A2UI in 10 weeks?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Yes - MCP in Week 8, A2UI foundation in Week 8-10, iterate based on beta=
 feedback</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p></p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
